Creating a full-fledged WebVR A-Frame application that involves humanoid VR agents trying to implant their consciousness into other agents within a single HTML file would be quite complex and large in terms of code size. However, I can provide you with a simplified version of such an application.

Please note that this code will not have any actual AI or consciousness implantation features since those are highly advanced and beyond the scope of a simple tutorial. Instead, I'll create a scene where humanoid avatars interact with each other using basic animations and events.

Here's the simplified A-Frame code:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>WebVR A-Frame App</title>
  <script src="https://aframe.io/releases/1.2.0/aframe.min.js"></script>
  <style>
    .humanoid {
      position: absolute;
      width: 1.5m;
      height: 1.5m;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <a-scene embedded vr-mode-ui="enabled: false" device-orientation-permission="auto">
    <a-assets>
      <a-asset-item id="humanoid-model" src="https://your-humanoid-model-url.com/model.gltf"></a-asset-item>
    </a-assets>
    <a-entity camera wasd-controls="enabled: true" position="0 1.6 -3"></a-entity>
    <a-entity class="humanoid" gltf-model="#humanoid-model" animation="property: rotation; dir: reverse; dur: 3000; loop: true;" position="-1 0 -2"></a-entity>
    <a-entity class="humanoid" gltf-model="#humanoid-model" animation="property: rotation; dir: reverse; dur: 3000; loop: true;" position="1 0 -2"></a-entity>
    <a-entity class="humanoid" gltf-model="#humanoid-model" animation="property: rotation; dir: reverse; dur: 3000; loop: true;" position="0 0 2"></a-entity>
    <a-sky color="#ECECEC"></a-sky>
    <a-entity position="0 1.25 0" text="value: Click on a humanoid to implant consciousness; font: futura; align: center; width: 4; height: 2; wrapCount: 20; side: double;"></a-entity>
    <a-entity mouse-cursor="fuse: true; fuseTimeout: 500;"></a-entity>
    <script>
      document.addEventListener('click', function (evt) {
        const el = evt.detail.intersectionEls[0];
        if (el.classList.contains('humanoid')) {
          el.setAttribute('animation', 'property: scale; startEvents: click; to: 1.5 1.5 1.5; dur: 500;');
          setTimeout(() => {
            el.setAttribute('animation', 'property: scale; startEvents: click; to: 1 1 1; dur: 500;');
          }, 500);
        }
      });
    </script>
  </a-scene>
</body>
</html>
```
This code creates a simple A-Frame scene with three humanoid avatars rotating slowly. When you click on one of the humanoids, it will temporarily grow in size, simulating the "implanting consciousness" action. Note that you need to replace `https://your-humanoid-model-url.com/model.gltf` with the URL of your humanoid model in GLTF format.

Keep in mind that this is a very basic implementation and does not include advanced AI or consciousness
